== Preparation ==

Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot of @water{to taste} for the rigatoni.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%grams}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

== Chicken and Pasta ==

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams}(diced) and bell pepper. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Cook until the chicken is browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Shift occasionally.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, add the @dried rigatoni{180%grams} to the #pot of boiling water and cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander and return to the #pot, off the heat. Mix in the @creme fraiche{65%grams} and season with salt and pepper.

== Sauce ==

Add the @dried thyme{1%sachet}, @chicken stock{1%sachet}, @water{25%ml} (double for 4p) and @passata{1%pack} to the pan with the chicken.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium. Season with salt and pepper.

Allow to simmer until the sauce has thickened and the veg is softened, stirring occasionally, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Loosen with a splash of water if the sauce is too dry.

== Assembly ==

Add half the parsley to the chicken and stir through.

Transfer the mixture to an #oven dish{} and top with the creamy pasta.

Cover with the @grated Italian style hard cheese{50%grams} and pop onto the top shelf of your #oven.

Bake until golden and a little crunchy at the edges, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Divide your creamy chicken pasta bake between plates or bowls.

Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining parsley.